Of course the expression ‘si paret, etc.' bas no formal or pro- cessual signification in Justinian; all that is meant is that a plaintiff cannot by a real action demand conveyance (datio) but merely recog- nition of his ownership or other ius in rem. For the anomaly of allowing a person whose property has been stolen the option between a real and a personal action see p. 507 supr.
